# Netlify Configuration for civilengineer Account

## Site Information
Account: civilengineer
Project: NOUFAL - نظام إدارة المشاريع الذكي
Repository: ahmednageh373-gif/ahmednagenoufal (or fork)

## Quick Setup Commands

### Option 1: Using Netlify UI (Recommended)
1. Visit: https://app.netlify.com
2. Login as: civilengineer
3. Click: "Add new site" → "Import project"
4. Select: GitHub repository
5. Deploy settings are auto-detected from netlify.toml

### Option 2: Using Netlify CLI
```bash
# Install CLI
npm install -g netlify-cli

# Login
netlify login

# Initialize site
cd /home/user/webapp
netlify init

# Deploy
netlify deploy --prod
```

## Build Configuration (from netlify.toml)
Build Command: npm run build
Publish Directory: dist
Node Version: 18

## Environment Variables (if needed)
Add in Netlify UI: Settings → Build & deploy → Environment

Example variables:
- VITE_API_KEY
- VITE_GEMINI_KEY
- VITE_APP_URL=https://ahmednagenoufal.com

## Custom Domain Setup
1. Domain: ahmednagenoufal.com
2. Netlify DNS or external DNS
3. CNAME record: www → [site-name].netlify.app
4. SSL: Auto-provisioned by Netlify

